This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Daniel W Honzik in court in person.  Attorney Jeffrey William Jensen in court in person for Daniel W Honzik.  Attorney Emily S Zimmel in court in person for State of Wisconsin. 

Case remains set for Jury Trial.  Witnesses subpoenaed.  No unusual Motions or Jury instructions to be filed.  All discovery and statements received. Case is adjourned for Jury Trial in Branch 6 on November 21, 2022.
Notice Of Expert Testimony, Received and Filed
State's Proposed Jury Instructions, Received and Filed
State's Witness List, Received and Filed

Attorney Jeffrey William Jensen in court for Daniel W Honzik.  Attorney Jessica Bellows for Emily S Zimmel in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Matter in court for an arraignment, however State has yet to file the amended information.  State was to file the amended information by 9/16.  No action taken.
Felony Pretrial Scheduling Order, signed and filed.

Defendant Daniel W Honzik in court with attorney Jeffrey William Jensen.   Jack T. Eichorst for Emily Zimmel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defense has received discovery and offer and reviewed with client..  Offer is placed on the record.   Offer rejected.  State to file an amended information by 9/16/2022.  Defense request a trial.  Arraignment scheduled for September 23, 2022 at 10:30 am.  Final pre-trial scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 08:30 am.
JusticePoint Supervision Report, received and filed.

Defendant Daniel W Honzik in court with attorney Jeffrey William Jensen.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin. PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 15, Judge J.D. Watts. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 15.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 17, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Daniel W Honzik in court with attorney Jeffrey William Jensen.  Emily S Zimmel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: nk
Case in Court for Indigency Hearing.  Court found the State has satisfied victims' rights law.  Indigency hearing proceeded.  Based upon the defendant's statements, the court found the defendant eligible for appointment of counsel at county expense.  The court appointed Attorney Jeffrey William Jensen to represent the defendant, and counsel accepted the appointment; counsel to be paid at the rate of $100.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant to repay Milwaukee County for attorney fees at the rate of $50.00 per month beginning on March 1, 2023 and then the 1st of each month there after.  Failure to make timely payments according to the imposed payment schedule may result in a civil judgment, subject to tax intercept.  Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense signed and filed.  Next court date scheduled for a Preliminary Hearing, by ZOOM.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 1, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Daniel W Honzik in court in person.  John Daniel Flynn appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for preliminary hearing. Defendant appears without counsel.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Watts, Branch 15.   Court orders the case adjourned for CAUSE for an Indigency Hearing.  Indigency hearing scheduled for May 25, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Justice Point Report received and filed.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.
No unsupervised internet access except for requirments of work and no unsupervised contact with minor children.

Defendant Daniel W Honzik in court with attorney Alejandro A Lockwood.  Defendant Daniel W Honzik in custody.  Adam Joseph Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Watts, Branch 15.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 5, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
